        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>baharat</strong> and your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add your <strong>sultanas</strong>, 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water </strong>and the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>mint </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce thickens into a gravy-like consistency and the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>Moroccan-style spiced lamb</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
